# Build Bible V2 — Chapter 2 (Architecture)

Spec: `docs/04_BUILD_BIBLE_V2_CHAPTER_02_ARCHITECTURE.md`

## Layering

- Business logic only in `src/lib/**` (services).
- Pages/layouts compose and orchestrate — no domain algorithms.
- Presentation components: no DB access, no business decisions.
- API routes stay thin — parse, authorize, delegate to services.
- Never import `server-only`, `@/lib/supabase/server`, or `@/lib/supabase/admin` into Client Components.

## Reuse

- One implementation per concern; consolidate duplicates.
- Remove dead modules, unused exports, unused dependencies.
- Do not move files without architectural justification.
- Do not invent unnecessary abstractions.

## Preserve

- Features, API contracts, DB contracts, RBAC, RLS, Paddle billing.
- Never reintroduce Stripe.

## This chapter

- Do not commit, push, or deploy from Chapter 2 work.
